  "market_context": "Natural Gas weekly chart formed a swing point with bullish bias targeting equal highs and failure swings above. The prior high fell shy of a relevant swing, framing the move as a retracement rather than a reversal, so the analyst sought continuation higher into the equal highs liquidity pool.",
  "key_observation": "Weekly swing point aligned with daily swing point, then on the hourly a V-shaped reversal with SMT formed near a protected swing — an ideal continuation signature for entering long toward the higher time frame draw on liquidity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a swing point on the weekly time frame with bullish bias toward overhead failure swings and equal highs.",
    "Step 2: Noted the prior high fell shy of a relevant swing, classifying the move as a retracement to be traded back into the equal highs rather than a reversal.",
    "Step 3: Required price to remain in the upper half of the range (avoiding a deep retrace into the lower fair value gap that would turn price bearish).",
    "Step 4: Waited for a daily swing point to confirm alignment with the weekly bias.",
    "Step 5: Dropped to the hourly time frame to look for protected swings, observing a V-shaped reversal with SMT confirmation.",
    "Step 6: Noted price opening near a protected swing — first potential positional entry with stop on the protected swing and target at the higher time frame equal highs (>2R).",
    "Step 7: After missing the first entry, identified a second setup — a sweep of a short-term low followed by another V-shaped reversal creating a new protected swing (intracandle CISD).",
    "Step 8: Evaluated 2R and ~4R targets toward the equal highs objective."
  ],
  "outcome": "First entry achieved 3.74R toward the target; the second entry would have been stopped out.",
  "lessons": "A V-shaped reversal paired with SMT and a protected swing is the ideal continuation signature after a higher time frame swing point forms. Multiple entry opportunities exist, but not all will work — disciplined stops on the protected swing and a >2R objective keep the strategy profitable.",
